_:N12f529d9e2aa46de90d53deb35060b24 <http://schema.org/headLine> "About us" .
<https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations> <http://schema.org/name> "Organisations" .
_:N12f529d9e2aa46de90d53deb35060b24 <http://schema.org/articleBody> "<div class=\"govspeak\"><h2 id=\"who-we-are\">Who we are</h2>\n\n<p>Government Skills brings together central Government teams responsible for civil servants’ and senior public service leaders’ learning and development.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"training-for-civil-servants\">Training for civil servants</h2>\n\n<p>We offer a full range of learning for civil servants which includes hundreds of online courses which are free and quick to access. </p>\n\n<p>Our quality assured <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/the-civil-service-recommended-curriculum\">curriculum of recommended learning</a> signposts civil servants to the courses that we believe matter the most and should be every civil servant’s first port of call when they consider their training needs</p>\n\n<p>It is searchable by course name via our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/the-civil-service-recommended-curriculum#a-to-z-of-the-best-free-courses-for-civil-servants\">A-Z of the best free courses</a> and also by subject area such Digital, data and innovation, leadership and management, writing skills and others.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"plans-for-a-national-school-of-government-and-public-services\"> Plans for a National School of Government and Public Services</h2>\n\n<p>On 20 January 2026, Chief Secretary to the Prime Minister Darren Jones announced <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/move-fast-fix-things-darren-jones-sets-out-plan-to-rewire-whitehall-and-incentivise-innovation-in-the-civil-service\">plans to establish the National School of Government and Public Services</a> to support our ambitions for a world-class, professional Civil Service. The new school will: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Align Civil Service training with government priorities, such as artificial intelligence, ensuring civil servants are properly skilled for a more digital approach to government.</li>\n  <li>Design and deliver more training in-house, removing duplication and reducing expenditure on external providers over time to provide better value for the taxpayer.</li>\n  <li>Introduce a new, streamlined curriculum for civil servants - giving them clarity about what skills they are expected to learn.</li>\n  <li>Invest in public sector leadership at the most senior levels, through place-based collaboration and expanding leadership development programmes.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"fast-stream-and-accelerated-development-schemes\">Fast Stream and accelerated development schemes</h2>\n\n<p>The <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.civil-service-careers.gov.uk/fast-stream/\">Fast Stream</a> is our flagship leadership and management programme. It is one of the UK’s top graduate schemes, and is regularly recognised by Times Top 100 Graduate Employer list. </p>\n\n<p>It ensures the Civil Service has a valuable, flexible pool of high-calibre trainees across all government professions and supports a pipeline of future talent.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"public-service-leaders\">Public service leaders</h2>\n\n<p>We offer events, courses and programmes to the most senior leaders of the largest public sector and civil service organisations.</p>\n\n<p>Our <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/public-sector-leadership-development\">National Leadership Forum</a> (NLF) brings together these leaders in the UK for an annual conference and a series of topical place-based events.</p>\n\n<p>The <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/guidance/public-sector-leadership-development\">Public Leaders Programme</a> welcomes CEOs for a 12 month programme focussed on systems leadership, managing crises across boundaries, and leading tomorrow’s organisations.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"college-for-national-security\">College for National Security </h2>\n\n<p>The College for National Security aims to break down barriers, deepen expertise, and build communities in National Security across the Civil Service and public sector. </p>\n\n<p>The College provides learning to colleagues at all levels of experience about the threats our country faces and how we can counter them. </p>\n\n<p>Through UK-wide learning and events, the College aims to improve responsiveness and effectiveness in countering increasingly hybrid threats and supports a growing community of national security practitioners in building their careers and networks.  .</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"contact-us\">Contact us</h3>\n\n<p>Contact the team at <a href=\"mailto:governmentskillscomms@cabinetoffice.gov.uk\">governmentskillscomms@cabinetoffice.gov.uk</a></p>\n</div>" .
